    "body": "> I would've expected eth.getBalance(\"0x3f5b715c30073534c52a1c9bab37cbcbbbb29f1e\", \"pending\") to return 0.\r\n\r\nNot sure that's a valid expectation. You would like `pending` to mean \"the state which would occur if we executed every single transaction that is currently pending\". I think it means \"the pending-state\", which is a block cobbled together containing _some_ of the pending transactions, according to tx-inclusion logic. If you were mining, that's the block you would be mining right now. \r\n\r\nSo it does not include all pending transactions, only a subset. @karalabe correct me if I'm wrong.  ",
